>>3c46fbef-7b3e-413d-ad63-5e8f65276e10
Since there's no centralized server, the way this works is that things that you post are shared with a number of users, to increase the chance that the data survives. Assuming that nobody opened your images before you left, and you shut down zeronet and cleared all your local files, it's possible that they would be gone. It seems to be a somewhat common issue on some of the boards for everything to have 0 seeds.
